[Name] VTK
[Summary] An open-source, freely available software system for 3D computer graphics, image processing and visualization.
[Description] The Visualization Toolkit (VTK) is an open-source, freely available software system for 3D computer graphics, image processing and visualization. VTK supports a wide variety of visualization algorithms including: scalar, vector, tensor, texture, and volumetric methods; and advanced modeling techniques such as: implicit modeling, polygon reduction, mesh smoothing, cutting, contouring, and Delaunay triangulation.
[License] BSD
[Homepage] http://www.vtk.org
